foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: The difference between the number of requests pending at the end of FY 2010 and the number pending at the beginning of FY 2011 is attributed to corrections to the business rules for calculating report data in the new Phase II of the EEOC FOIA Tracking System (FTS). The number of pending requests at the beginning of FY 2011 is correct. The number of pending requests at the end of FY 2010 was incorrect; the FTS database was updated during FY 2011 and an additional seventy-two FOIA requests were found.

foia:OtherDenialReason.foia:OtherDenialReasonDescriptionText: Suit not filed on charge (EEO reports)

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: The difference between the number of appeals at the end of FY 2010 and the number of pending appeals at the beginning of FY 2011 is attributed to corrections to the business rules for calculating report data in the new EEOC Phase II of the FOIA tracking system (FTS). The number of pending appeals at the beginning of FY 2011 is correct. The number of pending appeals at the end of 2010 was incorrect; the FTS database was updated during FY 2011 and found that 8 appeals were inaccurately counted.

foia:AppealDispositionAppliedExemptionsS.foia:FootnoteText: The difference between the number of appeals pending at the end of FY 2010 and the number pending appeals at the beginning of FY 2011 is attributed to corrections to the business rules for calculating report data in the new Phase II of theEEOC FOIA Tracking System (FTS). The number of pending appeals at the beginning of FY 2011 is correct. The number of pending appeals at the end of FY 2010 was incorrect. The FTS database was updated during FY 2011, and eight (8) appeals were found to have been incorrectly counted in the total number of appeals pending.

foia:OldestPendingRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: * There appears to be a glitch with the agency overall field for the 10th oldest FOIA. Unfortunately, it is not accepting our number of pending days (197); once the number is entered, it populates a date.

foia:PersonnelAndCostSection.foia:FootnoteText: EEOC expended $1,110 preparing a response brief to a FOIA lawsuit filed against the Memphis District Office.

foia:OldestPendingConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: EEOC did not receive any consultations from other agencies during FY2011.
